metadata.text: Spider-Man: Neighborhood Notes Original fan-made text comic script Issue 1: The Stolen Meteorite Panel 1 Night over Queens. Peter swings between apartment lights. PETER (thought): Rent is late, chemistry lab is early, and somehow crime still k eeps office hours. Panel 2 Police radios crackle below. DISPATCH: Suspect heading east on Roosevelt Avenue with a metal case. SPIDER-MAN: I love when the universe sends calendar invites. Panel 3 A masked thief sprints through traffic, clutching a glowing case. THIEF: Move! This rock is worth more than your whole block! SPIDER-MAN: Bold claim for a guy wearing bargain boots. Panel 4 Web line snaps across a streetlight and wraps the case. THIEF: Hey! SPIDER-MAN: Finders keepers, science edition. Panel 5 The case pops open in midair. A small meteorite pulses green. PETER (thought): That is not normal geologic behavior. Panel 6 Spider-Man lands on a fire escape as the meteorite hums louder. SPIDER-MAN: Note to self: never trust a rock with mood light

SPIDER-MAN: Note to self: never trust a rock with mood lighting. Panel 7 The thief lunges with a shock baton. THIEF: Hand it back! SPIDER-MAN: Counter-offer: you stop committing felonies. Panel 8 Spider-Man webs the baton and yanks it into a trash bin. SPIDER-MAN: Recycling is important. Panel 9 The meteorite emits a wave that flickers nearby streetlights. CROWD: Whoa! PETER (thought): If that surge hits the grid, Queens goes dark. Panel 10 Spider-Man wraps the meteorite in layered webbing and seals it inside the case. SPIDER-MAN: Improvised insulation. Please hold. Panel 11 Police arrive and cuff the thief. OFFICER: You again? SPIDER-MAN: You say that like I have hobbies. Panel 12 Dawn breaks. Peter hands the case to a city science team. PETER (thought): Maybe one good save can keep the lights on for everyone. End of Issue 1 Issue 2: The Rooftop Garden Heist Panel 1 Community rooftop garden, Saturday morning. MAY: The tomatoes are finally winning. PETER: Don't jinx the tomatoes, Aunt May. Panel 2 A drone swarm descends and starts cutting planter boxes loose. KID: Our garden! SPIDER-MAN: Okay, this is a new low for villainy. Panel 3 Spider-Man vaults over a skylight and tags three drones with web pellets. SPIDER-MAN: Unauthorized harvest denied. Panel 4 The drone controller appears on an adjacent roof in powered armor. VILLAIN: Soil data is money. You people sit on gold. SPIDER-MAN: It's basil and carrots, my guy. It's basil and carrots, my guy. Panel 5 Armor launches micro-rockets at water tanks. PETER (thought): If those tanks blow, the whole block floods. Panel 6 Spider-Man webs the rockets together mid-flight and swings them upward. SPIDER-MAN: Return to sender. Panel 7 The explosion showers sparks safely above the roofline. VILLAIN: Impossible! SPIDER-MAN: Strong disagreement from gravity and web fluid. Panel 8 Spider-Man short-circuits the armor using a hose and a webbed power cable. SPIDER-MAN: Conductive consequences. Panel 9 Neighbors secure the captured drones with garden twine. MAY: We can rebuild every planter by tomorrow. KID: Can Spider-Man come back for watering duty? Panel 10 Spider-Man salutes from the ledge before swinging away. SPIDER-MAN: Keep growing. This city needs more gardens than getaways. End of Issue 2
